      "date": "2015-02-14 03:09:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\nAbout the two test failures:\n- sanity-sec test_22: reported as LU-6247, the client was using 4K blocksize to estimate quota which was wrong. It's unlikely caused by this patch.\n- sanity-scrub: it failed at test preparation stage: \"mount lustre-ost1/ost1 at /mnt/ost1 failed: Cannot send after transport endpoint shutdown\"\n  There was not dmesg or logs collected so I'm not sure exactly why. But: 1) OI scrub test should be skipped for ZFS any way. 2) I ran sanity-scrub by hand 20 times: the scrub tests were skipped but no failure at preparation stages at all. So it's probably a consequence of the sanity-sec failure that happened before it.",
